# xlsx-js Project Standards

- Keep this package as a library-first setup with `type: module`.
- Build outputs must remain:
  - ESM: `dist/index.js`
  - CJS: `dist/index.cjs`
  - Types: `dist/index.d.ts`
- Source files live under `src/`.
- Prefer private class state over public mutable fields.
- Private fields use underscore naming (example: `_name`) and are exposed through getters.
- In classes that use `static` members: list every `static` method above the `constructor`, then instance methods (after fields, if fields are declared at the top of the class body).
- Keep ESLint passing, including private member underscore naming rules.
- Keep Prettier formatting consistent with repository `.prettierrc.json`.
- Releases are tag-driven (`vX.Y.Z`) and publish to GitHub Packages with tag/version alignment.
- Do not add implementation placeholders beyond minimal valid exports unless requested.
- If build or structure conventions change, update this rule file in the same change set.
